<div class="images">
    <h2 class="mb-4">Using <code>alt</code> attribute</h2>
    <img src="./../../img/logo-blue.svg" role="img" alt="Lisbon Digital School">

    <hr>

    <h2 class="mb-4">Using <code>aria-label</code></h2>
    <img src="./../../img/logo-blue.svg" role="img" aria-label="Lisbon Digital School">

    <hr>

    <p>Note: Please note that while ARIA can be used as a solution in certain cases, it is always preferable to prioritize the use of native HTML elements whenever possible. Native HTML provides built-in accessibility features and semantic meaning, ensuring better accessibility without relying heavily on ARIA attributes</p>

</div>
